                      The unique beauty of handicrafts                    The Crafts Council of India (CCI) is a voluntary organisation, working in the craft sector for the welfare of craftspeople and the development of handicrafts. CCI was established in 1976 by Kamala Devi Chattopadhyay and has its headquarters in Chennai. CCI is the apex body with a network of 10 affiliated state councils and is affiliated to the World Crafts Council, which is the only non-governmental international organisation working in the craft sector. Kamala, the retail outlet, offers a permanent window for quality crafts. Here products of excellence and quality are displayed, focusing on specially designed wares developed for the contemporary urban market. As the chill sets in the city gradually, Kamala gears up with its vast array of winter offerings to choose from this December. Patchwork bedcovers and table linen, pottery, shawls, stoles, scarves from Bhuj and Himachal Pradesh, bags, batuas, jholas, puppets and ceramicware  it packs in all this and much more. Also on show are plenty of items for Christmas shoppers. One can also pick up hand-made Christmas Tree decoratives here. Add to that their range of yards including hand-block printed tussars, Maheswaris and mulmuls.            Event: Christmas Bazaar, hosted by Kamala When: Till December 11; 10 am to 7 pm Where: Rabindranath Tagore Centre, ICCR, 9A Ho Chi Minh Sarani	                    
